Let $\mathcal{C}$ be a small, cofibrantly generated, simplicial model category whose underlying category is locally presentable, and suppose that the homotopy category $\mathrm{Ho}(\mathcal{C})$ satisfies the strong Whitehead property: for any two objects $X, Y \in \mathcal{C}$, if the induced map $\pi_n([X,Y]) \to \pi_n([X,Y'])$ is an isomorphism for all $n \geq 0$ and all $X$, then $Y \to Y'$ is a weak equivalence. Construct, assuming the consistency of a supercompact cardinal, a combinatorial model structure on the category of simplicial presheaves over a small Grothendieck site $\mathcal{S}$, denoted $\mathrm{SpSh}(\mathcal{S})$, such that:

(1) The weak equivalences are those maps $f: \mathcal{F} \to \mathcal{G}$ for which the induced morphism on homotopy sheaves $\pi_n(f): \pi_n(\mathcal{F}) \to \pi_n(\mathcal{G})$ is an isomorphism of sheaves for all $n \geq 0$;

(2) The cofibrations are the monomorphisms;

(3) The fibrant objects are precisely those simplicial presheaves $\mathcal{F}$ such that for every representable presheaf $h_U$, the mapping space $\mathrm{Map}(h_U, \mathcal{F})$ is locally Kan;

(4) The resulting homotopy category $\mathrm{Ho}(\mathrm{SpSh}(\mathcal{S}))$ is equivalent to the derived category $\mathbf{D}(\mathcal{S})$ of bounded below complexes of abelian sheaves on $\mathcal{S}$, and satisfies the Whitehead conjecture in the sense that every phantom map between fibrant objects is null-homotopic.

Prove that such a model structure exists if and only if the site $\mathcal{S}$ admits a basis closed under finite limits and satisfying the following higher coherence condition: for every finite diagram $D: I \to \mathcal{S}$, the Čech nerve $\check{C}(D)$ admits a homotopy colimit in $\mathrm{SpSh}(\mathcal{S})$ that is weakly equivalent to the homotopy colimit of the diagram $D$ in $\mathrm{Ho}(\mathrm{SpSh}(\mathcal{S}))$, and this equivalence is natural with respect to morphisms in $I$. Moreover, show that this condition is preserved under arbitrary small colimits of sites, and derive a necessary and sufficient condition for the existence of such a model structure in terms of the internal logic of the topos $\mathbf{Sh}(\mathcal{S})$, using only the language of constructive homotopy type theory with univalent universes and higher inductive types.
